<br>
the only things which need to be changed from a personal viewpoint: <br>
- there needs to be a <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>slightly</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> better selection of weapons for non-uber offensive melee. casual offensive melee arent doing enough damage relative to casual offensive casters.<br>
- even though verant has gone a long way towards fixing this issue and i commend them, melees <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>still</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> benefit more from high level equipment than casters do. more focus items are needed. uber casters still do not do enough damage relative to uber offensive melee really.<br>
- charm needs to be fixed. though it was always arguably too powerful, now its just out of control.<br>
- make grouping exp better/nerf solo exp. make mobs hit   even harder than they do currently, and have them give a little more exp. add a 7th slot to groups (to account for the influx of players who formerly were soloing).<br>
- snare should have a chance to break like root, from nukes/dots to limit wizard/druid soloing a little. not as much as root, but a small chance still. the idea is to still leave the option of soloing for classes who could do it before, but make grouping such a more attractive choice that they would only want to solo when they cant find a group.<br>
