<br>
I think this is one of the biggest class balance issues right now. The offensive melee non-uber weapon upgrades are just down right craptastic.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>- even though verant has gone a long way towards fixing this issue and i commend them, melees still benefit more from high level equipment than casters do. more focus items are needed. uber casters still do not do enough damage relative to uber offensive melee really.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
I do think there needs to be more focus items and things of that nature available to the masses, However I think casters on the damage side of things are ok. I think uber casters vs. uber melee is ok. If there is a problem it is non-uber casters doing comparable damage to uber melee, and in alot of cases exceeding them.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>- charm needs to be fixed. though it was always arguably too powerful, now its just out of control.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Nerfing charm is gonna affect mages how? I mean who cares really. I don't want to go around calling for any classes to be nerfed. Right now mages can reclaim pets to gain mana at a very fast rate. Some people say that isn't fair, but I don't see them calling for nerfs on there respect class boards. Last thing EQ needs is more nerfs.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>- make grouping exp better/nerf solo exp. make mobs hit even harder than they do currently, and have them give a little more exp. add a 7th slot to groups (to account for the influx of players who formerly were soloing).<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Again grouping experience is better then solo experience for most classes. Druids/Wizards and to a small point enchanters are the only classes that are soloing well in PoP. On TT server I don't see many people soloing in PoP so maybe that is why I don't understand all the bitching about kiters. I just don't see how crippling soloing for two classes that have the hardest time getting groups is gonna fix anything. I get 1 aa per hour in a 6 man group. Sorry but to me that is already border line &quot;to good&quot;. Maybe a small experience bonus but we don't need to expand groups or nerf soloing.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>- snare should have a chance to break like root, from nukes/dots to limit wizard/druid soloing a little. not as much as root, but a small chance still. the idea is to still leave the option of soloing for classes who could do it before, but make grouping such a more attractive choice that they would only want to solo when they cant find a group.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Noonie what you are missing is that most people solo because they can not find a group. I see lots of wizards LFG, and are not able to get one. So they go solo instead of waiting for the invite that is never gonna come. Nerfing things like snare has way more sweeping affects then to just soloing. You really need to calm down on this nerf yelling you been doing as of late.  By nerfing soloing you will cause more people to be LFG. There are not enough groups to support the number of people currently LFG. Just look at the number of people LFG during peek hours and you will see what I am talking about.<br>
<br>
Wezloc<br>
