But then again, I still think Mages are relatively under-equipped compared to their casting counterparts, especially Necromancers. The sheer amount of Summon spells that Mages receive as &quot;upgrades&quot; (Once you get to 50+, you've earned that special Mage spell that summons you your very own fishing pole. Geez, you guys are lucky) must make you guys feel as if Verant isn't making any effort at all. My younger brother has a 57 Mage, a pretty powerful character, but I can see that from the Mage perspective, your spells range from mostly fire-based damage (heavily resisted by wurms and the like) to Summoning knick-knacks to pass the time (Okay, I am exaggerating, your pets cause massive amounts of pain). <br>
